annotationA: Seryl-tRNA synthetase, mitochondrial (SerRS-m) catalyses the aminoacylation of tRNAser with serine, to be used for gene translation during protein synthesis
annotationB: Cysteine--tRNA ligase, cytoplasmic; tRNA binding; ATP binding; cysteine-tRNA ligase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: cysteinyl-tRNA aminoacylation
